{
  "id": "gen_1780159432518_ruins_on_the_roadside",
  "encounterTitle": "Toll on the Empty Road",
  "description": "Open grassland stretches across the map. A dirt path runs north to south; two ruins at the north-east and south-east.",
  "mapId": "gen_1780157947973_ruins_on_the_roadside",
  "npcIds": [],
  "allyIds": [],
  "enemyIds": [
    "bandit",
    "bandit"
  ],
  "customIntroduction": "The road between holdfasts has been quiet for too long. That kind of quiet means either the Bureau has finally stretched its patrols this far — or something worse has filled the gap. Two silhouettes step out from the scrub ahead, hands resting on weapon hilts, wearing the tired, hungry look of men who stopped waiting for honest work some seasons ago.",
  "customContext": "A stretch of open lowland road — the kind the Old Empire's engineers once warded against weather and banditry alike. The wards are long dead. Weeds push through the cracked stone, and the surrounding scrub has grown tall enough to hide a man crouching. Two bandits have claimed this strip as their toll-point, working travellers lean enough to rob and small enough not to fight back. They look like they've been at it long enough to be bold, and hungry enough to be desperate — a combination that makes them unpredictable.\n\nThe terrain offers thin cover in the scrub to either side of the road's centre. There is no Bureau patrol within earshot. Whatever happens here stays between you and them.\n\nTriggers:\n1. On encounter start (T0 announcement), a terse full-screen title card sets the scene — \"Two figures block the road ahead.\"\n2. When the player moves into the central road zone (T1 combat), the bandits drop any pretence of negotiation and attack.\n3. When the encounter is completed (T2 xp), the player is awarded 50 XP and the AI GM narrates a brief closing beat about the silence returning to the road.",
  "objective": "Defeat or drive off the two bandits blocking the road.",
  "completionFlag": "bandit_toll_cleared",
  "generated": true,
